'''Chadi Riad Dnanou''' ({{langx|ar|شادي رياض دنانو}}; born 17 June 2003) is a professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Defender (association football)#Centre-back|centre-back]] for {{English football updater|CrystalP}} club [[Crystal Palace F.C.|Crystal Palace]]. He plays for the [[Morocco national football team|Morocco national team]].

==Club career==
===Barcelona===
====Early career====
Born in [[Palma de Mallorca]], Balearic Islands to Moroccan parents, Riad represented CD Atlético Rafal, [[RCD Mallorca]] (two stints) and CD San Francisco before agreeing to a three-year deal with [[FC Barcelona]] in February 2019, effective as of July 2019.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ultimahora.es/deportes/real-mallorca/2019/02/15/1058337/chadi-riad-otra-joya-escapa.html|title=Chadi Riad, otra joya que se escapa|trans-title=Chadi Riad, another pearl who slips away|publisher=[[Última Hora (Spain)|Última Hora]]|language=es|date=15 February 2019|access-date=11 January 2021}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.sport.es/es/noticias/futbol-base/barca-ficha-joya-marroqui-del-mallorca-7294996|title=El Barça ficha a la joya marroquí del Mallorca|trans-title=''Barça'' sign the Moroccan pearl of Mallorca|publisher=[[Sport (Spanish newspaper)|Sport]]|language=es|date=10 February 2019|access-date=11 January 2021}}</ref>

====2020–21: Loan to Sabadell====
In 2020, Riad moved to [[CE Sabadell FC]] on loan for one year, being assigned to the ''Juvenil A'' squad.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cesabadell.cat/es/noticia/el-juvenil-a-estrena-la-temporada-en-division-de-honor|title=El Juvenil 'A' estrena la temporada en División de Honor|trans-title=''Juvenil 'A{{'}}'' start the season in the División de Honor|publisher=CE Sabadell FC|language=es|date=31 October 2020|access-date=11 January 2021}}</ref> He made his senior – and first team – debut on 16 December 2020, starting in a 2–0 away win against [[CD Ibiza Islas Pitiusas]], for [[2020–21 Copa del Rey|the season]]'s [[Copa del Rey]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.mundodeportivo.com/futbol/sabadell/20201216/491133980912/0-2-el-sabadell-espera-al-final-para-eliminar-al-pitiuses-de-la-copa.html|title=0–2, El Sabadell espera al final para eliminar al Pitiuses de la Copa|trans-title=0–2, Sabadell wait until the end to knock out {{sic|nolink=y|Pitiuses}} from the Cup|publisher=[[Mundo Deportivo]]|language=es|date=17 December 2020|access-date=11 January 2021}}</ref>

Riad's [[Segunda División]] debut occurred on 11 January 2021, as he came on as a late [[Substitute (association football)|substitute]] for [[Aleix Coch]] in a 1–1 home draw against [[CD Lugo]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.marca.com/futbol/segunda-division/sabadell-vs-lugo/cronica/2021/01/11/5ffccc10268e3e605e8b4579.html|title=El Sabadell deja escapar dos puntos en el último minuto|trans-title=Sabadell let two points slip in the last minute|publisher=[[Marca (newspaper)|Marca]]|language=es|date=11 January 2021|access-date=11 January 2021}}</ref>

====2022–23: B-team and first team debut====
On 5 July 2022, Riad renewed his contract with ''Barça'' until 2024, and was promoted to [[FC Barcelona Atlètic|the reserves]] in [[Primera Federación]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.sport.es/es/noticias/futbol-base/chadi-riad-sera-blaugrana-2024-14007825|title=Chadi Riad será blaugrana hasta 2024|trans-title=Chadi Riad will be ''blaugrana'' until 2024|publisher=[[Sport (Spanish newspaper)|Sport]]|language=es|date=5 July 2022|accessdate=9 July 2023}}</ref> He scored the winning goal on the season-opener match on 27 August, netting his side's third in a 3–2 home win over [[CD Castellón]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fcbarcelona.cat/ca/futbol/barca-b/noticies/2765277/barca-atletic-cd-castellon-marquez-sestrena-amb-un-triomf-dinfart-3-2|title=Barça Atlètic – CD Castellón: Márquez s'estrena amb un triomf d'infart (3–2)|trans-title=''Barça'' Atlètic – CD Castellón: Márquez debuts with a heart-stopping triumph (3–2)|publisher=FC Barcelona|language=ca|date=27 August 2022}}</ref>

Riad made his first team – and [[La Liga]] – debut for Barcelona on 8 November 2022, replacing goalscorer [[Pedri]] late into a 2–1 away success over [[CA Osasuna]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fcbarcelona.com/en/football/first-team/news/2899454/chadi-riad-makes-fc-barcelona-debut|title=Chadi Riad makes FC Barcelona debut|publisher=FC Barcelona|date=8 November 2022|accessdate=9 July 2023}}</ref> He was an undisputed starter for [[Rafael Márquez]]'s B-side during [[2022–23 Primera Federación|the campaign]], scoring three goals in 37 matches overall as the side missed out promotion in [[2023 Primera Federación play-offs|the play-offs]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.sport.es/es/noticias/barca/planes-barca-chadi-riad-89598326|title=Los planes del Barça con Chadi Riad|trans-title=The plans of ''Barça'' with Chadi Riad|publisher=[[Sport (Spanish newspaper)|Sport]]|language=es|date=7 July 2023|accessdate=9 July 2023}}</ref>

====2023–24: Loan to Betis====
On 26 July 2023, Riad joined [[Real Betis]] on a season-long loan deal with a mandatory option to buy for €3&nbsp;million.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.realbetisbalompie.es/noticias/actualidad/chadi-riad-sexta-incorporacion-del-real-betis-para-la-proxima-temporada-29270|title=Chadi Riad, sexta incorporación del Real Betis para la próxima temporada|trans-title=Chadi Riad, Real Betis sixth signing for the upcoming season|publisher=[[Real Betis]]|language=es|date=26 July 2023|accessdate=26 July 2023}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Menzies |first=John |url=https://www.football-espana.net/2024/04/06/barcelona-to-re-sign-defender-for-net-price-of-e4m-immediate-sale-anticipated-for-e15m |title=Barcelona to re-sign defender for net price of €4m, immediate sale anticipated for €15m |publisher=Football España |date=6 April 2024 }}</ref>

===Crystal Palace===
On 14 June 2024, [[Premier League]] club [[Crystal Palace F.C.|Crystal Palace]] announced the signing of Riad on a five-year contract, for a reported fee of £14m including add-ons.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.cpfc.co.uk/news/announcement/crystal-palace-sign-moroccan-defender-chadi-riad/ |title=Crystal Palace sign Moroccan defender Chadi Riad |publisher=Crystal Palace F.C. |date=14 June 2024 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/articles/cd11rp5rglgo |title=Palace sign centre-back Riad in £14m deal |publisher=BBC Sport |date=14 June 2024 }}</ref> His debut season was severely disrupted by injury; having made his first senior appearance against [[West Ham United F.C.|West Ham United]] in August 2024, he sustained a knee injury in his second outing, in the [[EFL Cup]] against [[Norwich City F.C.|Norwich City]], which kept him sidelined for over three months.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.cpfc.co.uk/teams/first-team/defender/chadi-riad/ |title=Chadi Riad |publisher=Crystal Palace F.C. |access-date=28 May 2026 }}</ref> Upon his return in late December 2024, he suffered a further knee injury in January 2025 which ruled him out for the remainder of the 2024–25 season, restricting him to just three appearances in total.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.inkl.com/news/crystal-palace-rocked-by-major-chadi-riad-injury-blow-to-alter-transfer-plans |title=Crystal Palace rocked by major Chadi Riad injury blow to alter transfer plans |date=27 January 2025 |access-date=28 May 2026 }}</ref>

Riad returned to first-team action on 25 January 2026, coming off the bench in a 3–1 home defeat to [[Chelsea F.C.|Chelsea]], and assisted [[Chris Richards (soccer)|Chris Richards]]' late consolation goal shortly after his introduction.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.cpfc.co.uk/news/match-reports/live-blog-report-highlights-crystal-palace-chelsea-january-2026/ |title=Report & Highlights: Palace undone by clinical Chelsea |publisher=Crystal Palace F.C. |date=25 January 2026 |access-date=28 May 2026 }}</ref> He started the [[2026 UEFA Conference League final]] on 27 May, playing the full 90 minutes in a three-man backline as Palace defeated [[Rayo Vallecano]] 1–0 in [[Leipzig]] to claim the club's first ever European trophy.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.sportsmole.co.uk/football/crystal-palace/europa-conference-league/news/crystal-palace-vs-rayo-vallecano-confirmed-xis-huge-wharton-richards-decisions-made-for-conference-league-final_598278.html |title=Crystal Palace vs. Rayo Vallecano confirmed starting lineups |publisher=Sports Mole |date=27 May 2026 |access-date=28 May 2026 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefaconferenceleague/news/02a5-20ba50a7a602-983af582dc90-1000--crystal-palace-1-0-rayo-vallecano-jean-philippe-mateta-wi/ |title=Crystal Palace 1–0 Rayo Vallecano: Jean-Philippe Mateta wins Conference League for the Eagles |publisher=UEFA |date=27 May 2026 |access-date=28 May 2026 }}</ref>

==International career==
Riad represented [[Morocco national under-20 football team|Morocco]] at [[Morocco national under-20 football team|under-20 level]] in 2022, scoring in a friendly against [[Romania national under-20 football team|Romania]] on 29 March. On 13 March 2023, he was called up to the full squad by manager [[Walid Regragui]], for friendlies against [[Brazil national football team|Brazil]] and [[Peru national football team|Peru]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=13 March 2023 |title=Regragui unveils his Atlas Lions list for March friendlies |url=https://en.hespress.com/60152-regragui-unveils-his-atlas-lions-list-for-march-friendlies.html |access-date=13 March 2023 |website=HESPRESS English – Morocco News |language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Aamari |first=Oussama |title=Walid Regragui Announces Morocco's Squad for March Friendlies |url=https://www.moroccoworldnews.com/2023/03/354435/walid-regragui-announces-moroccos-squad-for-march-friendlies |access-date=13 March 2023 |website=moroccoworldnews |language=en}}</ref> Riad also featured with the [[Morocco national under-23 football team|under-23 team]] in the [[2023 U-23 Africa Cup of Nations]], appearing in two matches as the side lifted the trophy.

Riad made the final squad for the senior [[Morocco national football team|Morocco national team]] at the [[2023 Africa Cup of Nations]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.newarab.com/news/morocco-selects-mix-youth-and-experience-afcon-squad|title=Morocco selects mix of youth and experience for AFCON squad|first=The New Arab Staff &|last=Agencies|date=29 December 2023|website=www.newarab.com/}}</ref> He debuted with Morocco in a 3–1 pre-tournament friendly win over [[Sierra Leone national football team|Sierra Leone]] on 11 January 2024.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://todaytimeslive.com/sports/475210.html|title=Chadi Riad, starter in Morocco's last friendly|date=12 January 2024|website=Today Times Live}}</ref>

